      "effects": [],
      "folder": null,
      "system": {
        "description": "<p><em><strong>Shields </strong></em>come in two general varieties. Small ones, often made of metal, can be strapped to the wearer&rsquo;s arm and allow them to hold and manipulate objects with that hand. Larger shields require the use of a gripping hand, but are usually of cheaper, lighter wood.</p>\n<p>A <em><strong>small shield</strong></em> user has a base AC of 13, while a <em><strong>large shield</strong></em> user has a base AC of 14. Unlike other armor, however, if the user is already wearing equal or better armor the shield grants a +1 bonus to their AC. Shields allow the bearer to ignore the first instance of Shock they might otherwise suffer in a round.</p>",
